WEBVTT

00:20.188 --> 00:22.147
[man whistles]

00:22.148 --> 00:24.024
Hey, Frank! Let's
wrap it up and go home.

00:24.025 --> 00:25.359
What do you say?

00:25.360 --> 00:27.444
Well, I got another
hour's work to do.

00:27.445 --> 00:30.030
The kid's gonna stick with me,
and then I'll show him the ropes.

00:30.031 --> 00:31.949
Okay. You lock up for
me before you go?

00:31.950 --> 00:34.410
4th of July weekend, buddy boy.
Got to move.

00:34.411 --> 00:36.578
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
Well, you have a nice 4th,

00:36.579 --> 00:38.747
and I'll see you Sunday
at the barbecue.

00:38.748 --> 00:41.500
You'd better believe it.
I'll be there with bells on.

00:41.501 --> 00:44.670
Kid, I wanna tell you something,
and I mean this sincerely.

00:44.671 --> 00:47.798
No matter what happens,
don't name it after me.

00:47.799 --> 00:49.259
[laughs]

00:49.884 --> 00:51.594
Take it easy, Frank.

00:52.804 --> 00:54.638
That Burt's a joker.

00:54.639 --> 00:56.557
OK, Freddy, follow me
and learn something.

00:56.558 --> 00:58.225
Okay.

00:58.226 --> 01:00.769
We got an order here from the St.
Louis University Medical School.

01:00.770 --> 01:03.939
They want two adult female
skeletons with perfect teeth.

01:03.940 --> 01:06.734
That's a 2-AF-PT.

01:06.735 --> 01:08.736
OK? So you come over
here to the "A" section.

01:08.737 --> 01:10.904
- That's "A" for adult, see?
- Okay.

01:10.905 --> 01:13.198
Then that's divided up
into two sections.

01:13.199 --> 01:15.951
That's divided into the "M"
for male and the "F" for...

01:15.952 --> 01:17.870
- Female.
- Good boy.

01:17.871 --> 01:19.538
Now the "PT."

01:19.539 --> 01:22.374
Suppose you think that's
"pretty tough", but no, that's...

01:22.375 --> 01:25.210
- Perfect teeth.
- Very good.

01:25.211 --> 01:28.005
Now you get some excelsior over
there and lay it in that crate.

01:28.006 --> 01:31.134
Make a nice little beddy-bye
for this little lady.

01:32.052 --> 01:33.136
Okay.

01:34.345 --> 01:36.555
Good work. We want
her to be comfortable.

01:36.556 --> 01:38.682
Now help me get her in.
Grab her legs.

01:38.683 --> 01:40.225
Okay.

01:40.226 --> 01:43.562
Now you get some of
that styrofoam popcorn,

01:43.563 --> 01:45.898
spread it all around.

01:45.899 --> 01:49.109
Don't be stingy.
Uncle Burt's paying for this.

01:49.110 --> 01:52.029
More, Freddy, more.
OK, that's fine.

01:52.030 --> 01:54.865
Now spread it around.
That's right.

01:54.866 --> 01:57.534
- You're doing very nice work.
- Thanks.

01:57.535 --> 01:59.578
You're gonna be fine in the
warehouse business.

01:59.579 --> 02:01.371
Where do we get all
these skeletons from?

02:01.372 --> 02:03.916
- Oh, they come from India.
- India?

02:03.917 --> 02:06.835
International treaty.
All skeletons come from India.

02:06.836 --> 02:08.252
No kidding. How come?

02:08.253 --> 02:09.880
How the hell do I know "how come"?

02:09.881 --> 02:11.799
The important question is,

02:11.800 --> 02:14.134
where do they get all the
skeletons with perfect teeth?

02:14.135 --> 02:16.136
I'm going to ask you a
serious question.

02:16.137 --> 02:18.305
How many people you know die

02:18.306 --> 02:21.767
with a beautiful, perfect set
of choppers in their puss, huh?

02:21.768 --> 02:23.435
Nobody I can think of.

02:23.436 --> 02:26.772
No. I think that there's a
skeleton farm over in India.

02:26.773 --> 02:28.982
[laughs]
Jesus!

02:28.983 --> 02:32.277
Come on, kid.
Follow your uncle here.

02:32.278 --> 02:33.904
Here we go.

02:33.905 --> 02:35.864
I don't have to tell
you what these are for.

02:35.865 --> 02:37.283
Ba ba ba boom!

02:38.159 --> 02:41.453
Here we've got the prosthetic
devices, all around here.

02:41.454 --> 02:43.664
Look under there. Wheelchairs.

02:43.665 --> 02:45.582
Right. These are great.

02:45.583 --> 02:47.084
Here's something you
don't see very often.

02:47.085 --> 02:49.128
You're a privileged person.

02:49.129 --> 02:52.756
These are split dogs.
Yep, for veterinarian schools.

02:52.757 --> 02:54.675
Oh, we get a lot of
orders for split dogs.

02:54.676 --> 02:55.843
- That's really rad.
- Yeah.

02:55.844 --> 02:58.887
[growls]
Don't fool around, you're learning.

02:58.888 --> 03:02.891
Over here, Freddy, is where
we keep the fresh cadavers.

03:02.892 --> 03:04.810
We sell these to medical schools

03:04.811 --> 03:07.397
and to the U.S. Army
for ballistic tests.

03:13.736 --> 03:15.280
Well, say hello.

03:24.330 --> 03:26.623
We usually got
more inventory than this,

03:26.624 --> 03:29.544
but, ah, we're expecting
a shipment on Monday.

03:31.504 --> 03:34.089
H-how many bodies are in here usually?

03:34.090 --> 03:36.258
Well, you know, you don't
want to be overstocked.

03:36.259 --> 03:38.177
Kind of like the restaurant business,

03:38.178 --> 03:41.598
you don't want your inventory
to lose its freshness.

03:42.682 --> 03:44.641
[laughs]

03:44.642 --> 03:46.268
Tell you what I'll do, kid.

03:46.269 --> 03:48.479
Teach you how to fill
out these shipping forms.

03:50.607 --> 03:52.108
Look alive.

03:56.654 --> 03:59.990
- We gonna party tonight or what?
- Yeah, we are gonna party.

03:59.991 --> 04:01.450
Well, where?
Where we gonna party?

04:01.451 --> 04:04.161
- I don't know. Somewhere.
- Hey, we could go to the park.

04:04.162 --> 04:07.247
Oh, no, we can't. The cops will
shoot us if we go back to the park.

04:07.248 --> 04:08.874
And I ain't in no mood to die tonight.

04:08.875 --> 04:10.417
I like death.

04:10.418 --> 04:12.252
I like death with sex.
How 'bout you, Casey?

04:12.253 --> 04:14.546
- You like sex with death?
- Yeah, so fuck off and die.

04:14.547 --> 04:16.130
So, when we gonna
party tonight, Tina?

04:16.132 --> 04:17.257
Oh you guys,
that'd be really rad,

04:17.257 --> 04:19.134
but I'm supposed to meet Freddy
when he gets off work.

04:19.135 --> 04:20.844
Yeah, where you
supposed to meet him?

04:20.845 --> 04:22.512
At this medical supply warehouse
where he's working.

04:22.513 --> 04:24.848
Oh, no, he got a job?
What a dick.

04:24.849 --> 04:26.558
Shit, why didn't you say so?

04:26.559 --> 04:28.644
Why don't we all go pick Freddy up?

04:28.645 --> 04:30.772
Freddy always knows where
there's a place to party.

04:40.531 --> 04:41.990
Frank?

04:41.991 --> 04:44.117
Yeah, kid?

04:44.118 --> 04:47.454
What's the weirdest thing
you ever saw in here?

04:47.455 --> 04:48.997
Oh, kid,

04:48.998 --> 04:51.375
I have seen weird things come,

04:51.376 --> 04:54.169
and I have seen weird things go.

04:54.170 --> 04:56.421
But the weirdest thing I ever saw

04:56.422 --> 04:58.590
just had to cap it all.

04:58.591 --> 05:01.260
Oh, yeah? What's that?

05:01.261 --> 05:03.263
Let me ask you a question, kid.

05:04.722 --> 05:09.059
Did you see that movie,
Night of the Living Dead?

05:09.060 --> 05:11.019
Yeah, yeah, that's the
one where the corpses

05:11.020 --> 05:12.312
start eating the people, right?

05:12.313 --> 05:14.564
Sure. Wh-what about it?

05:14.565 --> 05:18.151
Did you know that movie
was based on a true case?

05:18.152 --> 05:20.696
Come on, you're shitting me, right?

05:20.697 --> 05:23.241
I've never been more serious in my life.

05:24.534 --> 05:25.659
That's not possible.

05:25.660 --> 05:28.495
I mean, they showed
zombies taking over the world.

05:28.496 --> 05:32.541
They changed it all around.
What really happened was

05:32.542 --> 05:36.628
back in 1969, in Pittsburgh,
at the V.A. hospital,

05:36.629 --> 05:38.797
there was a chemical spill

05:38.798 --> 05:41.216
and all that stuff

05:41.217 --> 05:44.052
kinda leaked down into the morgue

05:44.053 --> 05:46.305
and it made all the dead bodies

05:46.306 --> 05:48.473
kinda jump around as
though it was alive.

05:48.474 --> 05:50.017
What chemical?

05:50.018 --> 05:52.978
2-4-5-Trioxin,
it's called.

05:52.979 --> 05:56.356
It was to kinda spray on
marijuana or something.

05:56.357 --> 05:58.483
And the Darrow Chemical Company

05:58.484 --> 06:00.652
was trying to develop it
for the Army.

06:00.653 --> 06:04.239
And they told the guy who
made the movie

06:04.240 --> 06:08.327
that if he told the true story,
they'd just sue his ass off.

06:08.328 --> 06:11.663
So he changed all the
facts around.

06:11.664 --> 06:13.999
So what really happened?

06:14.000 --> 06:17.127
Well, they closed it all down, see,

06:17.128 --> 06:20.839
and the Army shipped all
that contaminated dirt

06:20.840 --> 06:23.925
and all those dead bodies out.

06:23.926 --> 06:26.763
And they kept it a secret. Shh.

06:27.764 --> 06:29.097
What...

06:29.098 --> 06:31.683
So how come you know about it?

06:31.684 --> 06:34.811
A typical Army fuck up.

06:34.812 --> 06:38.566
The Transportation Department
got the orders crossed,

06:39.817 --> 06:43.320
and they shipped those bodies here

06:43.321 --> 06:46.282
instead of to the
Darrow Chemical Company.

06:47.116 --> 06:49.410
[telephone rings]

06:51.746 --> 06:52.914
Hello?

06:53.748 --> 06:55.082
Oh, hi, honey.

06:55.083 --> 06:57.125
Uh, no, I'll be home in
about an hour.

06:57.126 --> 06:59.504
You keep the, uh,
pot roast hot, okay?

07:00.838 --> 07:04.592
Yeah, sure, I love you,
too, honey. Yeah. Kiss, kiss.

07:09.972 --> 07:11.599
Wanna see them?

07:13.559 --> 07:16.312
- See them?
- The corpses.

07:18.689 --> 07:20.440
What are you talking about?

07:20.441 --> 07:23.444
- They're down in the basement.
- No.

07:24.362 --> 07:26.822
- Come on.
- No way.

07:26.823 --> 07:28.491
[door creaks]

07:32.703 --> 07:35.747
Hey, mind the third step.
It's a bitch.

07:35.748 --> 07:37.833
You mean, they just brought
those bodies here and left them?

07:37.834 --> 07:39.543
Well, you know the Army.

07:39.544 --> 07:41.337
And they've been here
all this time?

07:41.921 --> 07:44.382
14 years, as I recall.

07:45.800 --> 07:47.301
No kidding?

07:49.637 --> 07:51.055
There they are.

07:52.223 --> 07:53.975
There's bodies in there?

08:01.023 --> 08:03.609
[squeaking]

08:12.535 --> 08:15.579
Oh, shit. Look at that.

08:15.580 --> 08:18.708
- You say that thing was alive?
- So they say.

08:24.881 --> 08:26.299
Oh, God.

08:27.383 --> 08:29.676
- Hey, these things don't leak, do they?
- Leak? Hell, no.

08:29.677 --> 08:32.972
These things were made by the
U.S. Army Corps of Engineers.

08:33.890 --> 08:36.726
Oh, fuck!
[coughs]

08:41.606 --> 08:43.316
[choking]

11:07.460 --> 11:10.004
[soft classical music plays]

11:17.720 --> 11:20.096
Hello, dear. How was your day?

11:20.097 --> 11:21.598
The usual, crap.

11:21.599 --> 11:23.350
Oh, I'm sorry.

11:23.351 --> 11:24.726
What's for dinner?

11:24.727 --> 11:26.853
Your favorite, lamb chops.

11:26.854 --> 11:28.564
I had them for lunch.

11:49.585 --> 11:52.712
Yes, it's me, checking in
from Station 3 at 1600--

11:52.713 --> 11:55.048
uh, make that 1601 hours.

11:55.049 --> 11:57.176
I'll be home all evening. Right.

12:02.473 --> 12:04.600
[ Phone dialing ]

12:11.190 --> 12:14.943
It's nerve-racking to live around
that equipment all the time.

12:14.944 --> 12:18.238
They have to be able to reach
me 24 hours a day, wherever I am.

12:18.239 --> 12:19.322
You know that.

12:19.323 --> 12:21.658
All that microwave
stuff affects my oven.

12:21.659 --> 12:24.035
When we find them, you can
have the equipment taken out.

12:24.036 --> 12:25.787
But when will you find them?

12:25.788 --> 12:27.915
Christ, Ethel, I don't know!

12:29.333 --> 12:31.210
Maybe we'll never find them.

12:35.965 --> 12:38.007
Look, we've been
through all this before.

12:38.008 --> 12:39.802
They could be anywhere.

12:40.845 --> 12:43.305
[hard rock music plays]

12:46.475 --> 12:47.976
Where the fuck we going, anyway?

12:47.977 --> 12:50.478
- To party!
- To pick up Freddy.

12:50.479 --> 12:52.188
Oh, yeah, what the fuck is
Freddy up to these days, anyway?

12:52.189 --> 12:54.607
- He got himself a job.
- Oh, no shit? What job?

12:54.608 --> 12:57.318
- He's a stockroom clerk.
- Yeah? That sounds like a shitty job.

12:57.319 --> 12:59.028
Well, it isn't the President
of the United States,

12:59.029 --> 13:00.864
but at least he makes
money to buy stuff.

13:00.865 --> 13:02.782
Oh, yeah, maybe he'll
buy something from me?

13:02.783 --> 13:04.909
He don't like your
kind of stuff, Suicide.

13:04.910 --> 13:07.662
How come you guys only come 'round
when you need a ride someplace?

13:07.663 --> 13:09.748
'Cause you one spooky
motherfucker, Suicide.

13:09.749 --> 13:11.876
Oh, you think I'm spooky, huh?
What the fuck!

13:13.794 --> 13:16.380
[bell sounds]
[all yelling]

13:24.346 --> 13:26.848
Man, what a hideous, ugly place.

13:26.849 --> 13:30.268
- I like it. It's a statement.
- Come on, let's go get the prick.

13:30.269 --> 13:32.395
- No.
- Why not?

13:32.396 --> 13:35.231
- You might freak out his boss.
- Well, that's not nice.

13:35.232 --> 13:38.067
Yeah, what does he think
we are, weird or something?

13:38.068 --> 13:40.403
- What time does Freddy get off?
- 10:00.

13:40.404 --> 13:42.238
I ain't sittin' here two
fuckin' hours.

13:42.239 --> 13:44.157
We could always go drive around.

13:44.158 --> 13:46.326
I don't got gas.
You wanna buy some gas, idiot?

13:46.327 --> 13:47.702
I was kidding.

13:47.703 --> 13:49.370
We could go fool around
in there for a while.

13:49.371 --> 13:51.831
You mean that cemetery? Ahh.

13:51.832 --> 13:53.625
Oh, let's do that.

13:53.626 --> 13:55.586
[engine roars]

14:11.685 --> 14:14.562
What do you want to do, Scuz,
turn over gravestones?

14:14.563 --> 14:16.773
No, I just want to look
around the graveyard.

14:16.774 --> 14:18.608
I ain't never seen one before.

14:18.609 --> 14:20.276
Ain't you never been to a funeral?

14:20.277 --> 14:21.861
I never knew nobody that died.

14:21.862 --> 14:23.780
I don't think
this is such a good idea.

14:23.781 --> 14:25.949
- What's that?
- Road flares, asswipe.

14:25.950 --> 14:28.618
- What do you want those?
- I just want to party.

14:28.619 --> 14:30.538
What are the road flares for?

14:36.377 --> 14:37.837
[Scuz laughs]

14:39.505 --> 14:41.215
[crickets chirp]

14:42.091 --> 14:44.509
This place is a mess.

14:44.510 --> 14:46.178
[crows squawk]

14:48.472 --> 14:50.181
This looks like your pad, Scuz.

14:50.182 --> 14:51.642
I heard that.

14:52.810 --> 14:54.895
[hard rock music plays]

15:01.986 --> 15:03.988
[coughs]

15:05.114 --> 15:06.490
Frank?

15:07.658 --> 15:09.243
[coughs]

15:13.372 --> 15:14.874
[coughs]

15:21.255 --> 15:22.464
[gagging]

15:24.133 --> 15:25.801
Are you okay, kid?

15:26.677 --> 15:28.929
I don't know. I don't--
I don't feel so good.

15:29.847 --> 15:31.599
Christ, what a stink.

15:32.808 --> 15:34.268
[coughs]

15:35.769 --> 15:37.812
What the hell
happened to the body?

15:37.813 --> 15:40.523
It must have melted
when it hit the air.

15:40.524 --> 15:42.443
Close the goddamn thing.

15:45.613 --> 15:46.822
[coughs]

15:53.454 --> 15:56.123
Christ, I never smelled
anything like that before.

15:58.667 --> 16:01.378
I think I'm gonna be sick.
[wretches]

16:02.338 --> 16:03.797
[vomits]

16:06.467 --> 16:07.885
[coughs]

16:17.811 --> 16:21.648
[coughing]

16:21.649 --> 16:24.317
Listen, I don't guess we'd
better tell Burt about this.

16:24.318 --> 16:26.361
It makes us look stupid
or something.

16:26.362 --> 16:28.321
I can still smell that stuff.

16:28.322 --> 16:30.740
It must either be in my nose,
either that or it's all over everything.

16:30.741 --> 16:34.243
Yeah, I'd better spray
some deodorant around here.

16:34.244 --> 16:35.621
[coughs]

16:36.205 --> 16:37.498
[coughs]

16:39.500 --> 16:40.876
[coughs]

16:43.045 --> 16:44.254
[coughs]

16:45.214 --> 16:46.507
Oh.

16:47.383 --> 16:49.802
[dog whimpers]
What was that?

16:51.887 --> 16:54.556
- Sounds like a dog.
- A dog?

16:55.724 --> 16:57.558
Wait a second. Listen. Listen.

16:57.559 --> 16:59.936
[dog panting]
You hear that?

16:59.937 --> 17:02.021
What the hell's going on here?

17:02.022 --> 17:03.440
[coughs]

17:06.652 --> 17:08.319
[dog panting]

17:14.576 --> 17:16.078
What's wrong with him?

17:17.162 --> 17:19.497
[dog whimpers]

17:19.498 --> 17:21.958
Oh, shit!
[both scream]

17:21.959 --> 17:23.585
What are we gonna do?

17:24.377 --> 17:27.296
We're gonna kill it!

17:27.297 --> 17:29.215
[dog yelps]

17:29.216 --> 17:31.467
What are you doing? Stop!

17:31.468 --> 17:32.802
[screams]

17:32.803 --> 17:34.512
[distant screaming]

17:34.513 --> 17:36.139
[pounding on door]

17:36.140 --> 17:37.265
Aah!

17:37.266 --> 17:38.976
Oh, Jesus! Jesus!

17:39.560 --> 17:41.395
[screaming]

17:41.770 --> 17:43.688
Are we fucked? What's happening?

17:43.689 --> 17:46.607
It's the cadaver! The cadaver!

17:46.608 --> 17:49.736
- What's it doing in there?
- I don't know. It sounds sore!

17:49.737 --> 17:51.487
Well, what are we going to do?

17:51.488 --> 17:53.656
- Lock it in.
- Yeah! Yeah!

17:53.657 --> 17:54.867
Oh, Jesus!

17:55.576 --> 17:57.995
Hurry! Jesus Christ!

17:59.413 --> 18:01.622
We gotta think! We gotta think!

18:01.623 --> 18:03.584
Come on, son, get in there!

18:04.376 --> 18:05.753
Oh, Jesus Christ!

18:06.545 --> 18:08.337
Are we going crazy?

18:08.338 --> 18:10.048
No, it's that crap from the tanks.

18:10.049 --> 18:12.842
The goddamn chemicals,
it's all over everything.

18:12.843 --> 18:14.469
Stupid asshole!

18:14.470 --> 18:16.345
Watch your tongue, boy,
if you like this job.

18:16.346 --> 18:17.513
Like this job?

18:17.514 --> 18:20.349
- Think! Think!
- We gotta call the cops.

18:20.350 --> 18:21.851
No, you don't want to
call the cops.

18:21.852 --> 18:23.644
You know what they'd do
to this company?

18:23.645 --> 18:26.355
- Who cares about the company?
- Well, think of our reputation!

18:26.356 --> 18:27.482
Fuck your reputation.

18:27.483 --> 18:28.858
Think! Think!

18:28.859 --> 18:31.027
What about the number
on the side of the tank?

18:31.028 --> 18:33.613
The one that said to,
"Call in case of an emergency."

18:33.614 --> 18:35.198
No, that's the Army.

18:35.199 --> 18:38.076
You don't want the goddamn
Army around this place.

18:38.077 --> 18:40.369
- Think!
- Well, what are we gonna do?

18:40.370 --> 18:43.624
What are we gonna do?
We're gonna call the boss.

18:56.845 --> 18:59.055
Burt? Frank.

18:59.056 --> 19:00.556
We have a little problem.

19:00.557 --> 19:01.934
[distant screaming and pounding]

19:03.185 --> 19:05.312
Do you ever fantasize

19:06.188 --> 19:08.731
about being killed?

19:08.732 --> 19:10.525
Never.

19:10.526 --> 19:12.276
Do you ever wonder

19:12.277 --> 19:15.738
about all the different ways of dying,

19:15.739 --> 19:17.990
you know, violently

19:17.991 --> 19:19.617
and wonder, like,

19:19.618 --> 19:23.287
what would be the most
horrible way to die?

19:23.288 --> 19:25.957
I try not to think about
dying too much.

19:25.958 --> 19:26.917
Mmm.

19:27.918 --> 19:29.545
Well, for me

19:30.754 --> 19:32.464
the worst way

19:33.382 --> 19:36.717
would be for a bunch of old men

19:36.718 --> 19:38.554
to get around me

19:39.221 --> 19:41.472
and start biting

19:41.473 --> 19:43.933
and eating me alive.

19:43.934 --> 19:45.227
I see.

19:45.644 --> 19:47.228
First,

19:47.229 --> 19:50.773
they would tear off my clothes.

19:50.774 --> 19:52.400
<i>Let's get some light over here.</i>

19:52.401 --> 19:54.528
<i>Trash is taking off her clothes again.</i>

19:56.697 --> 19:58.656
♪ In darkness you will find me ♪

19:58.657 --> 20:00.950
♪ I dance among the dead ♪

20:00.951 --> 20:02.869
♪ But very soon I'll need to hunt ♪

20:02.870 --> 20:04.912
♪ The scent of blood instead ♪

20:04.913 --> 20:07.039
♪ Tonight ♪

20:07.040 --> 20:10.502
♪ We'll make love 'till we die ♪

20:12.504 --> 20:15.047
♪ Tonight ♪

20:15.048 --> 20:16.591
♪ We'll make love 'til... ♪

20:16.592 --> 20:18.176
That's right. Throw it, baby.

20:18.177 --> 20:20.636
Hey, are you high on anything?

20:20.637 --> 20:22.847
♪ I know you think I'm nasty ♪

20:22.848 --> 20:24.891
♪ But I am no common girl ♪

20:24.892 --> 20:26.893
♪ I once slept with the devil ♪

20:26.894 --> 20:28.895
♪ It was really no big thrill ♪

20:28.896 --> 20:31.272
♪ Tonight ♪

20:31.273 --> 20:34.610
♪ We'll make love 'til we die ♪

20:35.694 --> 20:36.819
You did what?

20:36.820 --> 20:38.196
You opened it? You stupid moron.

20:38.197 --> 20:39.906
You idiot. What's the
matter with you, Frank?

20:39.907 --> 20:41.866
Haven't I always told
you never to even

20:41.867 --> 20:43.492
go near those goddamn tanks?

20:43.493 --> 20:45.203
[screaming and pounding]

20:45.204 --> 20:46.787
What are we gonna do, Burt?

20:46.788 --> 20:47.914
I'll tell you what I'm gonna do.

20:47.915 --> 20:49.749
I'm gonna be sued by the
Darrow Chemical Company,

20:49.750 --> 20:51.542
I'm gonna be investigated
by the government.

20:51.543 --> 20:53.836
I might become famous, Frank,
I might even lose my business.

20:53.837 --> 20:55.755
I might even go to jail,
goddamn it.

20:55.756 --> 20:57.299
That's what I'm gonna do.

20:58.175 --> 21:00.135
[banging on door]

21:02.554 --> 21:06.265
On the other hand, we destroy
all this evidence around here

21:06.266 --> 21:07.683
and we keep our mouths shut.

21:07.684 --> 21:10.354
That's it! Let's do that, Burt!

21:10.729 --> 21:13.857
Yeah, Frank, you're right.
That's what we got to do.

21:14.608 --> 21:16.567
One question, Frank.

21:16.568 --> 21:20.112
This guy screaming in here,
you're sure he's a dead cadaver?

21:20.113 --> 21:22.615
Why don't you open
the door and find out?

21:22.616 --> 21:24.992
I'm sorry, Frank.
I'll take your word for that.

21:24.993 --> 21:28.996
If it is a reanimated body, we're
going-- we'll have to kill it.

21:28.997 --> 21:30.248
[screaming]

21:30.249 --> 21:31.958
How do you kill something
that's already dead?

21:31.959 --> 21:34.710
Well, how do I know, Fred?
I don't know, let me think.

21:34.711 --> 21:37.088
It's not a bad question, Burt.

21:37.089 --> 21:39.382
In that movie, they destroyed
the brain to kill them.

21:39.383 --> 21:42.010
- Is that what they did?
- The brain, right. Yeah.

21:43.637 --> 21:45.638
What do doctors use
to crack skulls with?

21:45.639 --> 21:48.307
- Surgical drills.
- Here, hold this, Frank.

21:48.308 --> 21:49.976
Now listen to me,
both of you, very carefully.

21:49.977 --> 21:51.560
Freddy, you're gonna
open that door.

21:51.561 --> 21:54.438
Come here, you stand right
over here. Frank, right here.

21:54.439 --> 21:56.399
When it comes out,
you brain it with that axe.

21:56.400 --> 21:57.900
Oh, Jesus!

21:57.901 --> 22:00.152
Well, how am I gonna
stop it from moaning?

22:00.153 --> 22:01.821
What's the matter with you, Frank?

22:01.822 --> 22:04.490
Fred, come here. Get down
there. Please, stand by the door.

22:04.491 --> 22:06.284
It's gonna be all right, son.

22:06.285 --> 22:08.536
I don't think I can do this, Burt.

22:08.537 --> 22:10.663
Well, you damn well better.
You got us into this.

22:10.664 --> 22:12.249
Oh, Jesus!

22:13.583 --> 22:15.918
All right, Freddy. 22, right.

22:15.919 --> 22:17.337
[door shaking]

22:18.005 --> 22:19.672
[moaning]

22:19.673 --> 22:20.881
Oh!

22:20.882 --> 22:22.759
Be brave, Frank, goddamn it!

22:23.635 --> 22:25.053
4, left.

22:27.764 --> 22:29.557
10, right.

22:29.558 --> 22:31.309
[door shaking]

22:31.310 --> 22:32.769
[moaning]

22:37.816 --> 22:39.859
[corpse screams]

22:39.860 --> 22:41.652
Aah!

22:41.653 --> 22:43.530
[corpse screams]

22:44.281 --> 22:45.615
Get him off, Frank!

22:45.949 --> 22:47.367
Aah!

22:49.703 --> 22:51.370
[crash]

22:51.371 --> 22:52.998
[all yell]

22:57.252 --> 22:58.795
[all scream]

23:00.505 --> 23:02.173
Coming, Frank.

23:02.174 --> 23:03.883
Hold it!

23:03.884 --> 23:05.343
Aah!

23:05.344 --> 23:07.220
[corpse screams]

23:08.180 --> 23:09.930
Oh!

23:09.931 --> 23:12.016
What the hell's going on, Burt?

23:12.017 --> 23:14.060
The brain! The brain!

23:14.061 --> 23:15.519
I hit the fucking brain!

23:15.520 --> 23:19.482
Then do something else, for
goddamn-it-to-hell's sake.

23:19.483 --> 23:21.901
Hold him down, Frank.

23:21.902 --> 23:25.446
I can't stand this any longer.

23:25.447 --> 23:27.990
- Oh, shit!
- Hold him down, now, hold him down,

23:27.991 --> 23:30.535
What are you gonna do? Oh!

23:33.497 --> 23:35.748
Be a man, Frank! Be a man!

23:35.749 --> 23:37.709
I can't stand this, you son of a bitch.

23:38.210 --> 23:39.878
Hurry up!

23:41.004 --> 23:42.589
[Frank screams]

23:43.215 --> 23:44.925
Oh, God!

23:48.970 --> 23:50.514
[all scream]

24:00.982 --> 24:03.109
- I'll get him!
- Get him!

24:03.110 --> 24:05.653
- I got him.
- Get a rope!

24:05.654 --> 24:07.196
Where the fuck's a rope?

24:07.197 --> 24:09.031
I don't know.
Get one. Hold him down!

24:09.032 --> 24:10.366
- Are you hanging on?
- Got him!

24:10.367 --> 24:12.118
Hang on to the son of a bitch!

24:12.119 --> 24:14.161
Christ, it ain't dying.

24:14.162 --> 24:17.206
I thought you said if we
destroyed the brain, it'd die!

24:17.207 --> 24:19.917
- It worked in the movie.
- Well, it ain't working now, Frank.

24:19.918 --> 24:21.710
You mean the movie lied?

24:21.711 --> 24:23.213
Oh, Jesus.

24:24.423 --> 24:25.674
Ah!

24:28.385 --> 24:30.052
How are we gonna kill it?

24:30.053 --> 24:32.305
Maybe you can't kill it.
Maybe it won't die.

24:36.226 --> 24:38.102
Then we just got to
destroy it completely

24:38.103 --> 24:39.520
until there's nothing left.

24:39.521 --> 24:41.021
Acid.

24:41.022 --> 24:43.357
What kind of acid would
dissolve a body?

24:43.358 --> 24:44.942
Sulfuric acid, maybe.

24:44.943 --> 24:48.237
No, no, aqua regia,
that's stronger.

24:48.238 --> 24:50.823
But what if it doesn't dissolve
everything, like the bones?

24:50.824 --> 24:52.700
[moans]

24:52.701 --> 24:53.994
Shit!

24:55.287 --> 24:57.247
What are we gonna do?

24:58.707 --> 25:00.000
Burt?

25:00.459 --> 25:01.918
Where are you going?

25:04.963 --> 25:07.798
Sometimes Ernie Kaltenbrunner
works late on Friday nights.

25:07.799 --> 25:09.675
Well, who's Ernie Kaltenbrunner?

25:09.676 --> 25:12.511
He's the embalmer at the
mortuary across the street.

25:12.512 --> 25:14.472
What the hell's
he gonna do for us?

25:14.473 --> 25:16.224
His light's on. He's in.

25:19.060 --> 25:21.395
Ernie's got a crematorium
across the street, Frank.

25:21.396 --> 25:24.106
A crematorium, that's beautiful.

25:24.107 --> 25:26.358
You think you can get
him to go along with it?

25:26.359 --> 25:28.486
I don't know. I've known
Ernie about 25 years.

25:28.487 --> 25:30.446
He might do it out of
friendship. I'm not sure.

25:30.447 --> 25:32.740
Yeah, but what the hell
are you gonna tell him?

25:32.741 --> 25:35.367
I mean, can you trust that bastard?

25:35.368 --> 25:38.329
I don't think we have a choice, Frank.

25:38.330 --> 25:41.082
How we--how we gonna get
this thing over there?

25:47.756 --> 25:49.715
Give me the bone saw.

25:49.716 --> 25:51.885
[hard rock music plays]

25:53.637 --> 25:56.555
Why don't you put your
clothes on? The show's over.

25:56.556 --> 25:59.476
What's the matter?
does it make you nervous?

26:00.727 --> 26:02.145
I'm hot.

26:03.188 --> 26:05.231
Yeah. You are hot.

26:05.232 --> 26:06.691
Scram, wimp.

26:12.864 --> 26:15.282
Nobody understands me,
you know that?

26:15.283 --> 26:18.452
I fuckin' bust my ass for
you guys, and what do I get?

26:18.453 --> 26:20.621
"You're spooky."

26:20.622 --> 26:22.915
Fuck you, man. Fuck you all.

26:22.916 --> 26:25.501
I like it spooky.

26:25.502 --> 26:27.419
I mean, I got somethin'
to say, you know?

26:27.420 --> 26:29.255
What do you think this is all about?

26:29.256 --> 26:31.215
You think this is a fuckin' costume?

26:31.216 --> 26:32.925
This is a way of life!

26:32.926 --> 26:34.511
Oh, yes.

26:36.555 --> 26:38.597
Hey, what's wrong with you, man?

26:38.598 --> 26:41.309
Show some fucking respect
for the dead, will ya?

26:45.397 --> 26:47.523
- Hey, is that Freddy?
- Where?

26:47.524 --> 26:49.275
Over there,
going in the building.

26:49.276 --> 26:51.444
Nope. That is not Freddy.

26:52.195 --> 26:53.737
How would you know?

26:53.738 --> 26:56.491
Because. Why would Freddy
be going into a mortuary?

26:58.827 --> 27:01.037
[classical music plays]

27:33.236 --> 27:35.614
[knock at door]

27:37.741 --> 27:39.659
Damn!

27:48.293 --> 27:50.170
What do you say, Ernie?

27:56.134 --> 27:57.302
Hey, Ernie.

27:57.886 --> 27:59.303
Whoa!

27:59.304 --> 28:01.473
- Take it easy.
- Sorry, I didn't hear you.

28:02.766 --> 28:04.351
Fast on the draw.

28:04.851 --> 28:05.769
Whew.

28:07.187 --> 28:08.937
You are working late tonight.

28:08.938 --> 28:12.232
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Pretty much. Kind of...

28:12.233 --> 28:15.027
What time is it?
You want a cup of coffee?

28:15.028 --> 28:16.862
Uh, no. No, thank you. I'm all right.

28:16.863 --> 28:18.448
I do, and I need it.

28:22.202 --> 28:25.537
What, uh, what are-- what
are you doing there, Ernie?

28:25.538 --> 28:27.706
Breaking out the rigor mortis.

28:27.707 --> 28:28.792
Oh, yeah?

28:30.085 --> 28:31.378
Come here.

28:31.961 --> 28:34.046
- Huh?
- Come on.

28:34.047 --> 28:37.091
You see, rigor mortis
starts in the brain.

28:37.092 --> 28:39.677
And it spreads down
to the internal organs,

28:39.678 --> 28:42.096
and it finally settles in the muscles.

28:42.097 --> 28:43.515
[clears throat]

28:44.307 --> 28:45.933
It, uh,

28:45.934 --> 28:48.686
loosens up after a while,
but, uh, you can, uh,

28:48.687 --> 28:52.898
you can break it out
manually, as they say

28:52.899 --> 28:55.859
by flexing the muscles. See that?

28:55.860 --> 28:56.902
Yeah.

28:56.903 --> 28:59.071
You'll not find that
in a book, my friend.

28:59.072 --> 29:03.033
The embalming business is basically
passed on by word of mouth.

29:03.034 --> 29:06.579
I'll tell you, that's fascinating,
Ernie, that's really something.

29:09.541 --> 29:13.044
Well, he's dead now.
And I am bushed.

29:16.923 --> 29:19.967
Hey, uh, buddy boy. Uh,

29:19.968 --> 29:22.887
how long we been friends,
Ernie? About how long? About...

29:24.472 --> 29:27.599
- 25 years, give or take.
- Yeah.

29:27.600 --> 29:31.437
Uh, if I ask you a favor,
could you keep it quiet?

29:31.438 --> 29:33.272
Sure. What is it?

29:33.273 --> 29:35.232
Well, I'm gonna need
some help, Ernie,

29:35.233 --> 29:37.901
in a pretty big way, really.

29:37.902 --> 29:40.320
You can depend on me.
Why? What's wrong?

29:40.321 --> 29:44.616
Uh, I got a couple of my men out
here, y-you mind if I let them in?

29:44.617 --> 29:46.785
B-Burt, that's illegal.

29:46.786 --> 29:48.996
You can bring it on in now, please.

29:48.997 --> 29:52.500
Fred, you can put it right
over here. Right here.

29:55.712 --> 29:57.005
What is that?

30:00.800 --> 30:01.967
Right there, please.

30:01.968 --> 30:03.094
- Here?
- Yeah.

30:12.020 --> 30:13.313
I got to...

30:13.855 --> 30:15.023
Yeah.

30:17.692 --> 30:19.903
What the hell is in those bags?

30:21.279 --> 30:23.572
- Rabid weasels.
- What?

30:23.573 --> 30:25.866
What the hell are you
doing with rabid weasels?

30:25.867 --> 30:28.577
I was trying to explain it to
you. They came as a shipment.

30:28.578 --> 30:30.537
'Course, they weren't
supposed to be rabid,

30:30.538 --> 30:32.498
you know, but you know
how these things happen.

30:32.499 --> 30:34.082
No, I don't. How do they happen?

30:34.083 --> 30:35.959
Watch out! Watch out,
Ernie. Don't get bit.

30:35.960 --> 30:37.085
Yeah.

30:37.086 --> 30:39.338
Anyway, we got them,
and we need your help.

30:39.339 --> 30:40.672
How?

30:40.673 --> 30:42.633
We got to get rid of these things.

30:42.634 --> 30:45.177
Well, why don't you
call an animal shelter?

30:45.178 --> 30:47.095
Well, word'd get out,
hurt my business.

30:47.096 --> 30:49.097
You know, that's a
bad scene, rabies.

30:49.098 --> 30:50.516
I don't think so.

30:50.517 --> 30:53.435
I mean, so what?
You don't run a pet store.

30:53.436 --> 30:55.521
So, some lab animals got rabies.

30:55.522 --> 30:58.358
Come on, guys,
take them to the pound.

30:59.901 --> 31:01.193
Well, I just can't do that.

31:01.194 --> 31:03.112
You got to--you got to
take my word for it.

31:04.989 --> 31:06.824
What the hell do you
want me to do?

31:06.825 --> 31:09.743
- You have a crematorium, right?
- You wanna burn them?

31:09.744 --> 31:11.620
Yeah, that's what I
had in mind, actually.

31:11.621 --> 31:13.205
That's cruel.

31:13.206 --> 31:14.748
I can't think of anything else to do.

31:14.749 --> 31:18.252
Y-y-you just can't
burn animals alive.

31:18.253 --> 31:20.045
It's just too hideous.

31:20.046 --> 31:21.839
At least let me kill them first.

31:21.840 --> 31:24.425
Take 'em out in the parking lot,
and put 'em out of their misery.

31:26.386 --> 31:29.137
I don't think that'd work, Ernie.

31:29.138 --> 31:31.766
I don't‒I don't u-understand
what's going on. W-why not?

31:38.481 --> 31:40.566
Can you swear to keep a secret, Ernie?

31:40.567 --> 31:42.568
At this point, I don't know.

31:42.569 --> 31:44.152
No, no, y-you got to swear.

31:44.153 --> 31:46.321
You got to, or I
just-- I can't tell you.

31:46.322 --> 31:49.283
All right, I swear.

31:49.284 --> 31:50.660
Good.

31:54.873 --> 31:57.083
It's not weasels in the bags.

31:58.835 --> 32:00.879
No. No kidding. Look here.

32:10.847 --> 32:12.014
Oh!

32:12.015 --> 32:14.808
Get it off!

32:14.809 --> 32:17.061
Get it off! Get it off!

32:17.896 --> 32:19.062
Frank!

32:19.063 --> 32:20.315
[screams]

32:21.316 --> 32:22.609
[moans]

32:25.737 --> 32:27.487
I'm sorry, Ernie.

32:27.488 --> 32:29.866
No, it's all right.

32:30.742 --> 32:32.035
[clears throat]

32:35.997 --> 32:37.832
Ernie, we got a...

32:39.417 --> 32:41.627
We got a long story to tell you.

32:41.628 --> 32:43.795
Oh, great. Some party.

32:43.796 --> 32:46.256
What happened to Trash and Suicide?

32:46.257 --> 32:48.551
Probably getting it on somewhere.

32:50.094 --> 32:52.846
Don't even think it, Chuck.

32:52.847 --> 32:55.641
Oh, God, when's 10:00
gonna come?

32:55.642 --> 32:58.561
Hey, if you wanna split,
we could both go somewhere.

33:00.605 --> 33:04.107
You'd really like to do
it with me, wouldn't you?

33:04.108 --> 33:06.402
Hey, I mean, a girl like
you and a guy like me.

33:07.236 --> 33:09.112
Go choke a chicken.

33:09.113 --> 33:12.282
Oh, come on, Casey.
I was only kidding.

33:12.283 --> 33:14.493
Oh, great, here's your
friend and mine.

33:14.494 --> 33:16.454
Hey, fuck you, ball buster.

33:18.623 --> 33:21.084
Hey, my watch stopped.
What time is it?

33:27.465 --> 33:28.882
Going on 10:00.

33:28.883 --> 33:31.051
Oh, fudge. I'd better
get over and find Freddy.

33:31.052 --> 33:33.136
He's gonna be getting
off any time now.

33:33.137 --> 33:34.680
OK. Go ahead, we'll wait for you.

33:34.681 --> 33:36.766
- Don't go anywhere, okay?
- All right.

33:38.935 --> 33:41.144
[Spider chatters]

33:41.145 --> 33:42.355
[Casey laughs]

34:02.417 --> 34:04.085
[siren sounds]

34:33.322 --> 34:34.907
[ring]

34:37.034 --> 34:40.036
Come on, Freddy, where are you?

34:40.038 --> 34:41.413
Frankly, Burt,

34:41.414 --> 34:44.206
I think you acted precipitously
in cutting up the corpse.

34:44.208 --> 34:47.002
Well, you may be right,
I don't know, but I did it.

34:47.003 --> 34:49.213
So what--what are we
gonna do about it, Ernie?

34:51.132 --> 34:54.385
If I let you use the crematorium,
what's in it for me?

34:56.512 --> 34:58.097
What do you want?

34:59.891 --> 35:01.600
Well, uh,

35:01.601 --> 35:04.311
the way I see it,
this is a pretty big favor.

35:04.312 --> 35:06.480
Well, Ernie, you got it!
Whatever it is you want,

35:06.481 --> 35:08.775
so help me, I'll--
I'll do it. I promise.

35:12.320 --> 35:14.030
I'm sorry about that.

35:19.202 --> 35:20.495
[sighs]

35:37.929 --> 35:39.847
All right. Let's take
care of your problem.

35:48.523 --> 35:50.148
Yes siree,

35:50.149 --> 35:51.983
you're gonna owe me a big one.

35:51.984 --> 35:54.820
Now buddy-boy, you go get rid of
everything for me. Nothing left.

35:54.821 --> 35:57.031
- Is that right?
- Everything'll go.

36:01.452 --> 36:03.328
What about the bones?

36:03.329 --> 36:04.622
Bones are no problem.

36:05.540 --> 36:07.458
The hardest thing to burn
is the heart.

36:08.000 --> 36:09.960
The heart? Why?

36:09.961 --> 36:12.087
'Cause it's just one big,
tough muscle.

36:12.088 --> 36:14.631
Yeah, but Ernie, I
mean, come on. We don't--

36:14.632 --> 36:16.466
We don't want the heart
sticking around.

36:16.467 --> 36:18.385
Then I'll turn it up
hotter for the heart.

36:18.386 --> 36:20.428
And what about the split dogs?
They got to go, too.

36:20.429 --> 36:22.515
The split dogs will go, too.

36:26.102 --> 36:28.813
Come on, just give me a hand.
It's your mess.

36:31.357 --> 36:34.110
Oh.
[groaning]

36:35.820 --> 36:37.404
Some big favor.

36:37.405 --> 36:40.115
I can operate that goddamn thing.

36:40.116 --> 36:42.367
You're absolutely certain

36:42.368 --> 36:45.495
that this will get rid of
everything and do the trick?

36:45.496 --> 36:48.665
- I mean, nothing left?
- Nothing but a little pile of ashes.

36:48.666 --> 36:50.500
We don't even want the ashes, Ernie.

36:50.501 --> 36:54.463
Well, then I'll turn it up higher,
and we'll burn up the ashes, too.

36:57.592 --> 36:59.135
Dust to dust.

37:56.776 --> 37:59.110
- Oh, my radio.
- Come on, you guys.

37:59.111 --> 38:01.947
Let's get back to the car.
Damn it.

38:01.948 --> 38:03.157
Come on.

38:18.547 --> 38:19.757
Freddy?

38:20.925 --> 38:22.342
Anybody?

38:22.343 --> 38:24.803
Get the fuckin' top! Fuck.

38:24.804 --> 38:26.931
Get the fuckin' top, man!

38:29.392 --> 38:30.643
Come on!

38:32.895 --> 38:34.646
Close the motherfuckin' windows.

38:34.647 --> 38:37.066
I don't have any windows.
I busted them.

38:38.484 --> 38:41.403
- Hey, my skin burns.
- Me, too. Damn it.

38:41.404 --> 38:43.613
It's that rain,
it's like acid rain.

38:43.614 --> 38:45.156
Start the car!

38:45.157 --> 38:47.826
It's all over me. A towel,
somebody give me a towel.

38:47.827 --> 38:50.912
- We ain't got no towel!
- Well, then give me something.

38:50.913 --> 38:52.872
- Give me that.
- No!

38:52.873 --> 38:54.457
Give me something!

38:54.458 --> 38:55.834
Come on, start!

38:55.835 --> 38:58.795
- Suicide, get the car going.
- I'm trying.

38:58.796 --> 39:02.133
Oh, crap, I wonder what's
in that rain.

39:14.645 --> 39:16.480
Look at it.

39:16.689 --> 39:19.233
It's coming down like,
einen getrunken soldat.

39:47.345 --> 39:50.722
- Is the heart gone, Ernie?
- It's all burned up.

39:50.723 --> 39:53.224
- Are you sure?
- Right up the chimney.

39:53.225 --> 39:56.102
Goddamn, that's all we need.
We're home free, Frank.

39:56.103 --> 39:58.646
We got it made. You just
saved our ass, buddy boy,

39:58.647 --> 40:00.900
and I owe you one. Goddamn!

40:01.942 --> 40:03.485
Yes, you do.

40:03.486 --> 40:05.695
Alright, let's get back to that
warehouse, clean up the mess,

40:05.696 --> 40:07.072
and get the hell out of there.

40:07.073 --> 40:08.490
What do you say, Frank?

40:08.491 --> 40:10.325
Okay, just--just give
me a second to rest,

40:10.326 --> 40:12.202
catch my breath.
Then we'll do it, okay?

40:12.203 --> 40:14.955
Frank, I don't know about
you, but I'm really sick.

40:15.831 --> 40:17.791
Why? What's wrong, Fred?

40:17.792 --> 40:19.667
I feel like hell is what's wrong.

40:19.668 --> 40:22.296
- I'm really sick.
- I'm sick, too, Burt.

40:22.922 --> 40:24.923
Sick, like how?

40:24.924 --> 40:27.259
I feel like my head's
going to bust wide open.

40:28.803 --> 40:30.345
And I want to puke.

40:30.346 --> 40:32.013
And I'm weak, too.

40:32.014 --> 40:33.890
Me, too. I got the chills.

40:33.891 --> 40:35.266
It's that stuff, Burt.

40:35.267 --> 40:36.893
It's that goddamn stuff we breathed.

40:36.894 --> 40:39.020
What stuff? What are
you talking about, Frank?

40:39.021 --> 40:42.399
When that canister cracked,
this gas squirted out.

40:42.400 --> 40:44.651
It hit us right in the face.

40:44.652 --> 40:46.153
We breathed it.

40:47.113 --> 40:49.406
It knocked us out.

40:49.407 --> 40:51.408
We were out cold,
unconscious for a while.

40:51.409 --> 40:53.201
Oh, Christ! Ernie.

40:53.202 --> 40:55.537
Shouldn't we get to a doctor
or-- or something like that?

40:55.538 --> 40:57.122
Yeah, Burt, I need a doctor.

40:57.123 --> 40:58.206
Man, I'm getting the car

40:58.207 --> 41:00.291
and taking these guys to the
emergency ward right now.

41:00.292 --> 41:01.918
Let's go, Frank.
You're gonna be alright.

41:01.919 --> 41:03.503
We're gonna get you there.

41:03.504 --> 41:05.130
Hey, Frank!

41:05.131 --> 41:06.048
Frank!

41:07.466 --> 41:08.717
[wretches]

41:10.386 --> 41:11.845
[vomits]

41:11.846 --> 41:13.304
Come here, Ernie.

41:13.305 --> 41:16.642
What's the matter? Talk to me.
Get him out of the rain.

41:17.852 --> 41:22.730
I gotta‒I gotta call my wife.
I gotta go to the hospital!

41:22.731 --> 41:26.025
You can't run around in
this storm. You're too sick.

41:26.026 --> 41:27.153
Burt.

41:28.779 --> 41:31.281
Take it easy. Take it easy.

41:31.282 --> 41:32.574
I'm gonna call an ambulance.

41:32.575 --> 41:34.660
Paramedics. Paramedics.

41:37.246 --> 41:39.331
It's all right.
How do you feel now?

41:42.751 --> 41:44.670
[thunder claps]

41:45.379 --> 41:46.754
Hello. Yes.

41:46.755 --> 41:50.091
Uh, can we get some paramedics
over here right away?

41:50.092 --> 41:53.303
That's the Resurrection Funeral Home

41:53.304 --> 41:56.765
at 21702 East Central.

41:57.933 --> 42:01.479
Uh, well, tell them to come around
the back, to the embalming room.

42:03.022 --> 42:05.648
Uh, no, no, um...

42:05.649 --> 42:09.903
Poison. We have two men
poisoned here.

42:09.904 --> 42:12.114
Uh, well, no, we--we don't
know what kind of poison.

42:13.574 --> 42:15.241
Right.

42:15.242 --> 42:17.203
Thank you very much. Bye.

42:19.288 --> 42:21.247
Burt, they're on their way.

42:21.248 --> 42:23.042
[engine turning]

42:23.834 --> 42:25.293
This car ain't going nowhere.

42:25.294 --> 42:26.420
- Damn it.
- Shh-shh!

42:27.421 --> 42:29.547
Do you hear something?

42:29.548 --> 42:31.341
Hear what?

42:31.342 --> 42:33.301
Something.

42:33.302 --> 42:35.596
[distant moaning and wailing]

42:50.778 --> 42:52.655
[pounding]

43:00.913 --> 43:02.455
No, I don't hear nothing.

43:02.456 --> 43:03.915
This roof's leaking.

43:03.916 --> 43:06.084
- There's a rip, damn it.
- Shit.

43:06.085 --> 43:07.669
Oh, don't do that!

43:07.670 --> 43:09.087
- Shit!
- I'm sorry.

43:09.088 --> 43:10.922
Shit, Scuz!

43:10.923 --> 43:12.341
Hello, there?

43:12.925 --> 43:14.260
Freddy?

43:18.973 --> 43:20.474
Anybody?

43:35.823 --> 43:38.158
Freddy? Are you here?

43:41.161 --> 43:42.663
[creak]

43:57.344 --> 43:58.804
Anybody here?

44:23.787 --> 44:25.414
Who's there?

44:28.375 --> 44:29.835
Brains!

44:32.254 --> 44:33.839
Brains!

44:35.132 --> 44:37.050
[screams]

44:37.051 --> 44:38.760
Hey, I got to get out of here.

44:38.761 --> 44:40.470
Let's go to where
Tina and Freddy are.

44:40.471 --> 44:42.264
- Damn right.
- Fuckin' A.

44:43.849 --> 44:45.309
[gasping]

44:47.519 --> 44:49.104
Live brain.

44:50.481 --> 44:53.776
[screams]

44:57.237 --> 44:58.364
[screams]

45:05.037 --> 45:06.205
[screams]

45:12.586 --> 45:14.129
Come on, quick!

45:36.110 --> 45:38.445
God, my skin's really burning.

45:44.284 --> 45:45.953
[sobs]

45:48.205 --> 45:49.872
Hey, Tina!

45:49.873 --> 45:52.542
Yes! Oh, God! Help me!

45:52.543 --> 45:54.544
- That's Tina.
- What's she yelling about?

45:54.545 --> 45:56.296
- What's that sound?
- Through that door!

45:58.215 --> 46:00.217
Watch the fuckin' step!

46:00.718 --> 46:02.261
Help me!

46:02.636 --> 46:04.178
What the fuck?

46:04.179 --> 46:05.848
[Tina screeches]

46:09.393 --> 46:10.936
Brains!

46:14.398 --> 46:16.066
[screams]

46:24.324 --> 46:26.452
More brains.

46:33.584 --> 46:35.042
Where the fuck you going?

46:35.043 --> 46:37.962
Help me bar the door!
Stupid fuckers!

46:37.963 --> 46:40.466
[siren wails]

46:51.268 --> 46:52.811
[knock at door]

46:54.521 --> 46:55.981
It's them.

46:59.735 --> 47:01.235
Who took the poison?

47:01.236 --> 47:02.488
Right over there.

47:08.535 --> 47:10.662
Stick your tongue out for me.

47:18.921 --> 47:20.546
What did you guys take?

47:20.547 --> 47:23.341
It was some kind of industrial chemical,

47:23.342 --> 47:25.093
I think, something in a tank.

47:25.719 --> 47:27.720
What tank? Where?

47:27.721 --> 47:29.639
Well, we--we're
not sure, really.

47:29.640 --> 47:31.098
Well, can you find out?

47:31.099 --> 47:33.100
I mean, your friends'
lives may depend on it.

47:33.101 --> 47:35.561
Yeah, well, I got to
make some phone calls,

47:35.562 --> 47:38.064
but I‒I can't do that
before morning. I'm sorry.

47:38.065 --> 47:40.150
Let's take some vital signs.

47:43.320 --> 47:44.571
[squeezes pump]

47:47.699 --> 47:50.368
- Can I borrow your stethoscope?
- What's the matter?

47:50.369 --> 47:51.953
